Used 2 golden mangos to make 4 servings instead of persimmon, used rasberry vinegar, walnut oil and chopped caramelized walnuts (whole foods). Use 1 T oil and 1/2 T vinegar per serving. Slice prosciutto crosswise about 1 inch wide and weigh 1 ounce per serving. 1 T walnuts per serving. 1/2 oz arugula per serving 1 T pomegranate seeds per serving 1/2 golden ripe mango per serving. Fabulous! Read More http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/notes/Prosciutto-with-Persimmon-Pomegranate-and-Arugula-236768#ixzz1z2jgZ9gg

Rating: 4
I simplified the assembly by strewing arugula leaves over a large platter, tearing prosciutto over top, scattering slices of persimmon and pomegranate seeds over that... forgot the nuts, oops... and made vinaigrette with olive oil, pomegranate molasses, and a bit of agave syrup to take the edge off. Drizzled dressing over the whole platter at the table. It was so very festive for Thanksgiving!

